	<h2>Introduction:</h2>
	This lab exercises the ability to:
	<ul>
		<li>modify a Newton's Method algorithm</li>
		<li>perform semi-automatic iteration</li>
		<li>Demonstrate the convergence of Newton's Method</li>
	</ul>
	<h2>Lab Assignment:</h2>

	Modify <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs200/Reed/3rdEd/NewtonAlgorithmSqrtErrs.htm">Reed's Newton's Method code as augmented by Dr. Anda</a>
	to demonstrate the convergence of Newton's method to find the reciprocal [<b>1 / <i>y</i></b>]
	using the formula,<br>
	<b><tt>newApprox = oldApprox * ( 2 - <i>y</i> * oldApprox )</tt></b><br>
	Your Webpage should as closely as possible resemble
	<a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs200/screenshots/NewtonAlgReciprocalErrs.bmp">This screenshot</a>.
	    <p>
	    When finished (after you&rsquo;ve tested and proofread your Web page),<br>
	    then submit your files to the appropriate D2L dropbox.
